# Week-by-Week, Day-by-Day Guide (Aug 19 – Oct 18, 2025)

You have 8 hours/day. Every day includes:
- Python DSA (90m) and Advanced SQL (60m)
- Core labs for the weekly theme (135m)
- Fundamentals/Basics (45m) or catch-up
- System Design (45m) or documentation
- Certifications study (60m)
- Project work (45m on weekdays; 4–6h on weekends by reallocating blocks)

Abbreviations:
- DSA = Data Structures & Algorithms (Python)
- SQL = Advanced SQL
- Labs = Hands-on labs for the week’s primary topic
- Fund = Fundamentals/Basics (Linux, Git, Python packaging, networking, data modeling)
- SD = System Design
- Cert = Certifications (DBX-DEA, AWS SAA, AWS DEA)
- Proj = Weekly project tasks
- DBX = Databricks
- GE = Great Expectations

Tip: Keep a “mistakes log” and a small “perf notebook” for measurements. Use README-first for projects.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

WEEK 1: Tue Aug 19 – Sun Aug 24 (Foundations: Linux, Git, SQL Core, Python Baseline)
Goal: Get local environment ready; strong Linux/Git/Python/test baseline; deliver Postgres ETL+analytics.

Tue Aug 19
- DSA (90m): Arrays & Strings basics; solve 3–4 easy→medium; note complexity.
- SQL (60m): INNER/LEFT/ANTI joins; 2 queries with EXPLAIN/ANALYZE on Postgres.
- Labs (135m): Install Docker, Compose, Python 3.11, Poetry/pyenv; spin up Postgres in Docker.
- Fund (45m): Linux navigation, files/permissions, grep/sed/awk basics.
- SD (45m): Batch vs streaming overview; ingestion→staging→marts pattern.
- Cert (60m): SAA + DEA overview, exam domains; create flashcards (IAM, storage).
- Proj (45m): Project 1 spec (README-first): inputs (nginx/app logs), outputs, acceptance tests.

Wed Aug 20
- DSA: Hashing; 3–4 problems (frequency maps, anagrams, 2-sum variants).
- SQL: Window functions basics (row_number, rank, dense_rank); 2 queries.
- Labs: Python project skeleton (pytest, ruff/black, mypy); pre-commit; basic CLI with argparse.
- Fund: Git branching, PR, rebase vs merge; set up GitHub repo + Actions.
- SD: Idempotency and retries; write a small idempotent transform.
- Cert: SAA IAM primer (users/roles/policies, MFA); DEA storage overview.
- Proj: Set up Postgres schema: staging, cleaned, marts; ERD sketch.

Thu Aug 21
- DSA: Sliding Window; 3–4 problems (longest substring, subarray sums).
- SQL: Window frames, lag/lead; 2 queries with frames (rows between).
- Labs: Log parser (Python); parse→CSV/JSON; load to staging table.
- Fund: Linux processes, systemd timers vs cron; simple backup script with tar/gzip.
- SD: Backfills/reprocessing strategies; write re-run notes.
- Cert: SAA VPC basics (subnets, route tables, IGW/NAT); DEA Athena intro.
- Proj: Write SQL for sessionization and p95 latency; capture EXPLAIN.

Fri Aug 22
- DSA: Two Pointers; 3–4 problems (sorted arrays, three-sum, palindrome).
- SQL: Anti/semi joins; duplicates handling; NULL semantics.
- Labs: Indexing vs full scans on queries; add proper indexes and compare plans.
- Fund: Python typing/mypy, exceptions, logging basics.
- SD: Data contracts and schema evolution; write a JSON schema for logs.
- Cert: DEA Glue/Athena overview; SAA storage classes (S3 tiers).
- Proj: Unit tests for parser; Dockerfile; Makefile (test, format, run).

Sat Aug 23
- DSA: Linked Lists; 3 problems (reverse, detect cycle, merge).
- SQL: CTEs; 2 recursive CTEs (hierarchy/path) on small test data.
- Labs: Build small perf test (timings) for SQL queries; record numbers.
- Fund: Git hooks (pre-commit), PR template, CODEOWNERS (self); CI green.
- SD: Failure modes and DLQ/quarantine plan for bad rows.
- Cert: SAA HA/resilience basics (multi-AZ, ALB); DEA partitioning intro.
- Proj (4–5h): Integrate pipeline end-to-end; store execution plan screenshots.

Sun Aug 24 (Deliver Project 1)
- DSA: Stacks/Queues; 3 problems (valid parentheses, min stack, queue via stacks).
- SQL: Grouping sets/rollup/cube; 2 queries; compare scans.
- Labs: Final polish; add README diagrams (ERD, flow).
- Fund: Shell scripts for run/start/stop; env vars (.env.example).
- SD: SLA/SLOs; backfill steps; on-call notes.
- Cert: DEA practice 15–20 Q (storage/Athena); review misses.
- Proj (4–5h): Finalize tests, docs; tag v1.0; retrospective.

