How to adapt daily if you overrun
- Take time from Fund or SD blocks first.
- Keep DSA (90m) and SQL (60m) sacred whenever possible.
- Protect weekend project windows; that’s where portfolio value compounds.

Checklist to keep in your repo (copy into README)
- Daily: DSA done; SQL done; labs progress; notes logged; one perf/cost/security insight.
- Weekly: Project delivered with tests, quality gates, docs, diagrams; CI green; retrospective done.
- Certifications: One measurable step daily; timed practice weekly; two full-length before each exam.

Good luck—stick to the cadence, keep everything versioned, observable, and documented. Your portfolio will reflect senior-level habits.
